nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glutamate\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets glutamate as a central amino acid emerging from interconnected hydrothermal carbon fixation, surface cyanide/sugar chemistry, and biochemical transamination/reductive amination. Hydrothermal reactions generate C1-C3 hubs such as formate, acetate, pyruvate, and oxaloacetate equivalents; surface chemistry generates HCN-derived nitrogen carriers, aldehydes, sugars, and alanine/aspartate precursors; biochemical steps converge on alpha-ketoglutarate and glutamate through multiple amination and transamination routes. The design emphasizes hub molecules shared across environments: HCN, pyruvate, oxaloacetate, aspartate, and alpha-ketoglutarate.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetate) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H4O5 (oxaloacetate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H7NO4 (aspartate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C5H6O5 (alpha-ketoglutarate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C5H9NO4 (glutamate) [target]\n\nREACTIONS (12 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Greigite-catalyzed reduction of carbon dioxide to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_006, mol_007 (Magnetite-mediated C1 to acetate and formaldehyde network) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_007, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Surface photochemical generation of hydrogen cyanide) [Surface