nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glutamate\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The network targets glutamate through a chemically conservative prebiotic core centered on hydrothermal carbon fixation to C1-C3 intermediates, surface generation of aldehydes, cyanide chemistry, and biochemical assembly around an alpha-ketoglutarate hub. To avoid weak steps criticized previously, the network uses: (i) supported hydrothermal formation of formate, acetate, pyruvate, and oxaloacetate analogs on Fe-S and magnetite minerals; (ii) correct Strecker logic via aldehydes to aminonitriles followed by hydrolysis; (iii) convergent generation of aspartate from oxaloacetate and alanine from pyruvate; (iv) alpha-ketoglutarate formation by reductive carboxylation/chain extension from succinate or by oxidative deamination/transamination relationships rather than unsupported direct aspartate-to-alpha-ketoglutarate conversion; and (v) final glutamate formation by either reductive amination of alpha-ketoglutarate or transamination with alanine/aspartate-derived amino donors. Hydrothermal products feed surface chemistry, and surface products feed biochemical assembly, yielding 10 valid route combinations to glutamate through shared hubs: formate, pyruvate, oxaloacetate, alpha-ketoglutarate, and alanine.\n\nMOLECULES (17 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: NH3 (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_004: HCN (hydrogen cyanide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH2O2 (formate/formic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: C2H4O2 (acetate/acetic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C3H6O3 (glyceraldehyde) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: C3H4O3 (pyruvate/pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C3H7NO2 (alanine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H4O5 (oxaloacetate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H7NO4 (aspartate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: C4H6O4 (succinate/succinic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C5H6O5 (alpha-ketoglutarate/2-oxoglutarate) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_016: C5H9NO4 (glutamate) [target]\n  - mol_017: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (14 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_005 (Hydrothermal CO2 reduction to formate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_002: mol_005, mol_002 -> mol_007 (Hydrothermal formate reduction to formaldehyde equivalents) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_003: mol_007, mol_005 -> mol_008 (Fischer-Tropsch-type homologation to glycolaldehyde) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_004: mol_007, mol_008 -> mol_009 (Surface borate-stabilized formose step to glyceraldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_005: mol_005, mol_008, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_010 (Hydrothermal synthesis of pyruvate from C1/C2 feedstocks) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_006: mol_017 -> mol_004 (Surface photochemical entry to HCN) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_010, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_011 (Hydrothermal pyruvate reductive amination to alanine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_008: mol_004, mol_003, mol_007 -> mol_011 (Surface Strecker synthesis of alanine from acetaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_010, mol_001 -> mol_012 (Hydrothermal carboxylation of pyruvate to oxaloacetate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_010: mol_012, mol_011 -> mol_013, mol_010 (Biochemical transamination of oxaloacetate to aspartate) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_011: mol_012, mol_002 -> mol_014 (Hydrothermal reduction of oxaloacetate-class intermediates to succinate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_012: mol_014, mol_001, mol_002 -> mol_015 (Hydrothermal reductive carboxylation of succinate to alpha-ketoglutarate) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_013: mol_015, mol_011 -> mol_016, mol_010 (Biochemical transamination of alpha-ketoglutarate to glutamate using alanine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_014: mol_015, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_016 (Biochemical reductive amination of alpha-ketoglutarate to glutamate) [Biochemical]\n\nPATHWAYS (10):\n  - P1: Hydrothermal rTCA-like alanine transamination route (9 steps)\n  - P2: Hydrothermal rTCA-like direct reductive amination route (8 steps)\n  - P3: Surface sugar-assisted entry with alanine donor (10 steps)\n  - P4: Surface sugar-assisted entry with direct glutamate amination (9 steps)\n  - P5: Surface HCN-Strecker alanine donor route (9 steps)\n  - P6: Mixed hydrothermal-surface alanine convergence route (11 steps)\n  - P7: Aspartate-enabled network recycling route (10 steps)\n  - P8: Oxaloacetate-first direct glutamate route (8 steps)\n  - P9: Formate-centered dual convergence route (9 steps)\n  - P10: Maximum interconnection hydrothermal-surface-biochemical route (12 steps)\n\nHUB MOLECULES: mol_005, mol_010, mol_011, mol_012, mol_015\nCONVERGENCE POINTS: 5\n\n\nPlease evaluate the network and respond with JSON:\n{\n    \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n        {\n            \"pathway_id\": \"<id>\",\n            \"reaction_scores\": {\"rxn_001\": 0.85, ...},\n            \"chemical_feasibility\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"pathway_coherence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"environmental_progression\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"target_achievement\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n            \"feedback\": \"<pathway-specific feedback>\",\n            \"approved\": <true if confidence >= 0.8>,\n            \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_ids with issues\"],\n            \"suggestions\": [\"improvements\"]\n        }\n    ],\n    \"best_pathway_id\": \"<id of best pathway>\",\n    \"overall_confidence\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"network_feedback\": \"<overall assessment>\",\n    \"approved\": <true if any pathway approved>,\n    \"hub_quality\": <0.0-1.0>,\n    \"convergence_quality\": <0.0-1.0>\n}\n", "raw_response": "{\n  \"pathway_evaluations\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.58,\n      