7,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.85,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.78,\n      \"feedback\": \"One of the better pathways. The oxaloacetate-aspartate-alanine recycling logic is coherent and the transamination steps are strong. Confidence remains capped by the speculative oxaloacetate reduction and succinate carboxylation sequence to alpha-ketoglutarate.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Promote the aspartate branch as a donor/recycling module rather than implying direct carbon-chain conversion\",\n        \"Anchor alpha-ketoglutarate production in a more defensible mineral-mediated ketoacid network\",\n        \"Clarify whether oxaloacetate survives long enough in solution or is generated/consumed in situ\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_002\": 0.58,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.4,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.7,\n        \"rxn_009\": 0.62,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.52,\n        \"rxn_012\": 0.35,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.56\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.58,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.79,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.83,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.78,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.7,\n      \"feedback\": \"A compact route with good internal logic around oxaloacetate, but it remains heavily dependent on the weakest chain-extension chemistry and a less-supported final direct amination. Overall acceptable as a conceptual route, not yet convincing as a high-confidence prebiotic path.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_012\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Replace direct glutamate amination with transamination\",\n        \"Bolster evidence for oxaloacetate-to-succinate handling under hydrothermal conditions\",\n        \"Consi